    Models acceleration as a nonlinear harmonic oscillator with damping:
    a = params[0] * x0 + params[1] * (x0 ** 3) + params[2] * x1 + params[3]

    Typically:
    - params[0]: linear stiffness coefficient (negative)
    - params[1]: nonlinear stiffness coefficient (negative)
    - params[2]: damping coefficient (negative)
    - params[3]: constant offset (optional)

    Parameters:
        x0 (np.ndarray): Position at time t
        x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity at time t
        params (np.ndarray): Coefficients array with at least 4 elements

    Returns:
        np.ndarray: Acceleration at time t
    """
